5000|$|Following {{revisions}} to the act in 1946 creating the <b>Social</b> <b>Security</b> Administration, Altmeyer was appointed Commissioner for <b>Social</b> <b>Security.</b> Altmeyer was criticized for his policy <b>that</b> the <b>Social</b> <b>Security</b> Administration would help people get benefits they were entitled to. His critics found a law from 1835 saying that no officer of the Federal Government [...] "shall encourage a claim against the federal government".|$|R
